WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.237 --> 00:00:15.713
Shah Rukh Khan: "A girl should be seen, not heard."
沙鲁克·汗： “女子无才便是德”，

2
00:00:15.737 --> 00:00:17.463
"Be quiet," or, "chup."
“安静”， “不要多嘴"，

3
00:00:17.487 --> 00:00:21.171
These words are often used to silence girls right from childhood,
这些句子从小到大就用来

4
00:00:20.245 --> 00:00:22.470
well into adulthood
束缚女性，

5
00:00:22.528 --> 00:00:24.254
and deep into old age.
一直到晚年。

6
00:00:24.278 --> 00:00:27.921
I'm proud to introduce our next speaker, a true champion of the female voice,
我很荣幸介绍下一位演讲者， 她是一位女性发声的真正捍卫者，

7
00:00:27.945 --> 00:00:29.588
an advisor on poverty,
一位帮助世界银行、联合国，

8
00:00:29.612 --> 00:00:31.754
gender and development for the World Bank,
还有一些印度以及全世界 非政府组织的

9
00:00:31.778 --> 00:00:36.088
United Nations and several NGOs in India and the world over.
关于贫困，性别和发展的顾问。

10
00:00:36.112 --> 00:00:39.629
She calls herself a cultural detective.
她称自己为一名文化侦探。

11
00:00:39.653 --> 00:00:44.296
Let's raise our voices to welcome renowned social scientist and author
让我们用热烈的掌声欢迎 著名社会科学家和作家

12
00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:45.921
Deepa Narayan.
迪帕·纳拉扬。

13
00:00:45.945 --> 00:00:48.171
(Music)
（音乐）

14
00:00:47.987 --> 00:00:52.073
(Applause)
（掌声）

15
00:00:56.528 --> 00:00:58.713
Deepa Narayan: The goal of every loving parent
迪帕·纳拉扬： 每一位爱孩子的父母的目标

16
00:00:58.737 --> 00:01:00.588
is to raise good girls,
就是抚养一个好女孩，

17
00:01:00.612 --> 00:01:02.421
but what parents actually do
但是父母们往往做的

18
00:01:02.445 --> 00:01:06.963
is to constrain, confine and crush their girls.
却是束缚、局限、压制他们的女儿。

19
00:01:06.987 --> 00:01:08.838
So as they crush their girls,
当压制自己的女儿们时，

20
00:01:08.862 --> 00:01:10.778
they prepare them for abuse.
他们其实正在为她们 将来的忍气吞声埋下的隐患。

21
00:01:11.695 --> 00:01:13.879
This would be so devastating
这个现实太残酷，

22
00:01:13.903 --> 00:01:16.463
that no parent would be able to bear it,
没有父母愿意接受，

23
00:01:16.487 --> 00:01:17.754
so it's disguised.
所以它被伪装了起来。

24
00:01:17.778 --> 00:01:21.046
In India, we call this "adjusting."
在印度，这叫做“适应”。

25
00:01:20.853 --> 00:01:22.704
I'm sure you've heard the word.
我相信你们肯定听说过这个词。

26
00:01:23.445 --> 00:01:25.504
"Darling, just adjust a bit.
“亲爱的，适应了就习惯了。”

27
00:01:25.528 --> 00:01:26.796
Just adjust.
“只是适应而已。”

28
00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:29.796
No matter what happens, just adjust."
“不管发生什么事情， 只要适应了就好。”

29
00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:33.629
"Adjust" trains girls to be powerless,
“适应”让女子变得无力，

30
00:01:33.653 --> 00:01:36.213
not to exist, not to be seen,
不存在，不被关注，

31
00:01:36.237 --> 00:01:37.921
not to have a self,
没有自我，

32
00:01:37.945 --> 00:01:44.338
and it trains boys to claim power and authority over the world.
而这也锻炼男孩去争取 世界上的权利和地位。

33
00:01:44.362 --> 00:01:49.838
And in the meantime we keep talking about gender equality and women's empowerment.
与此同时，我们一直在讨论 性别平等和女性赋权。

34
00:01:49.862 --> 00:01:55.463
After 2012, after the gang rape in a moving bus in Delhi,
2012 年后， 在德里大巴轮奸事件后，

35
00:01:55.487 --> 00:02:00.504
I really wanted to understand the roots of abuse.
我想去真正地理解 这种虐待的根源。

36
00:02:00.528 --> 00:02:03.963
So I started asking a very simple question:
于是我开始问一个很简单的问题：

37
00:02:03.987 --> 00:02:09.278
what does it mean to you to be a good woman or a good man today?
对你而言，在当代世界怎样做 才能算是一个好女人，好男人？

38
00:02:10.153 --> 00:02:13.046
And I was so surprised by what I heard,
我对自己听到的答案感到很惊讶，

39
00:02:12.950 --> 00:02:16.250
the answers particularly that young people gave,
尤其是年轻人给出的答案，

40
00:02:16.445 --> 00:02:22.004
that the project became a research project and it took over my life.
于是这个小课题变成了 一个我全身心投入的研究性项目，

41
00:02:21.921 --> 00:02:27.354
For three years, I listened to over 600 women, men and children,
在 3 年中，我收集了 超过 600 名男女老少的答案，

42
00:02:27.487 --> 00:02:29.296
educated, middle class,
包括受过教育的，中产阶级的，

43
00:02:29.320 --> 00:02:33.379
and it led to 1,800 hours of listening
总计 1,800 小时的录音，

44
00:02:33.403 --> 00:02:35.713
and 8,000 pages of notes,
和 8,000 页的笔记，

45
00:02:35.737 --> 00:02:38.171
and it took another year to make sense of it.
又花了一年的时间分析内容。

46
00:02:38.195 --> 00:02:44.254
Nowadays, we see well-dressed, educated women like many of you in this room,
在这个房间里坐着的 像你们一样衣冠楚楚且博学的女性，

47
00:02:44.278 --> 00:02:47.088
all of you in this room, and myself,
你们所有人，还有我，

48
00:02:46.957 --> 00:02:49.450
and we think the world has changed,
我们相信这个世界已经改变了，

49
00:02:49.695 --> 00:02:53.504
but these external changes are extremely misleading,
但是这些外表上的变化 很容易误导我们，

50
00:02:53.528 --> 00:02:56.487
because on the inside, we have not changed.
因为问题的本质一点都没有变。

51
00:02:58.195 --> 00:03:00.629
So today, I'm not going to talk about poor people.
今天我要讲的不是穷人。

52
00:03:00.653 --> 00:03:03.588
I'm going to talk only about the middle and upper classes,
我接下来要讲的是中上阶级的人，

53
00:03:03.612 --> 00:03:06.713
because we are the ones most in denial.
因为我们是最否认这一点的人。

54
00:03:06.737 --> 00:03:10.838
We are the ones who have said over and over again
我们一遍一遍地在说

55
00:03:10.862 --> 00:03:13.004
that when women are educated,
当女性受过教育，

56
00:03:12.912 --> 00:03:14.478
when they're employed
当她们进入职场，

57
00:03:14.403 --> 00:03:16.713
and they earn incomes,
当她们养家糊口的时候，

58
00:03:16.737 --> 00:03:19.445
they will be equal, empowered and free.
她们就会变得平等， 被赋权，且自由。

59
00:03:20.487 --> 00:03:21.879
They're not.
但是并没有。

60
00:03:21.903 --> 00:03:23.171
Why?
为什么？

61
00:03:23.195 --> 00:03:26.838
From my research, I identify seven habits
从我的研究中， 我识别并总结了

62
00:03:26.862 --> 00:03:28.421
that delete women,
让人们对女性

63
00:03:28.445 --> 00:03:30.629
that make women disappear,
视而不见的七种习惯。

64
00:03:30.653 --> 00:03:33.254
but these habits persist
但是这些习惯一直存在，

65
00:03:33.278 --> 00:03:35.671
because they're so familiar to us
因为我们对它们太熟悉了，

66
00:03:35.695 --> 00:03:37.778
and we've made them good and moral.
我们把它们看成好品德。

67
00:03:38.612 --> 00:03:42.195
Why would you change or drop anything that's good and moral?
我们为什么要改变好习惯呢？

68
00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:45.379
So, on the one hand, we love our children,
我们一边在爱自己的孩子，

69
00:03:45.403 --> 00:03:46.713
we love our daughters,
爱护我们的女儿，

70
00:03:46.737 --> 00:03:49.112
and on the other hand, we crush them.
但是也在一边压制她们。

71
00:03:50.695 --> 00:03:53.445
Habit one: You don't have a body.
习惯一：你没有一个身体。

72
00:03:54.905 --> 00:04:00.256
The first step to make a girl a ghost is to make her body disappear,
要让一个女孩感觉她不存在的 第一步就是让她的身体消失，

73
00:04:00.362 --> 00:04:02.588
to pretend that she doesn't have a body.
假装她没有一个身体。

74
00:04:02.612 --> 00:04:05.463
Akangsha, who is 23, said,
23 岁的 Akangsha 说，

75
00:04:05.487 --> 00:04:09.838
"In my family, we never spoke about the body, never."
“在我的家里，我们从来 不谈论自己的身体，从来不。”

76
00:04:09.862 --> 00:04:11.463
And it is in this silence
也就是在这样的死寂中，

77
00:04:11.487 --> 00:04:15.379
that millions and millions of girls get sexually molested,
上百万的女孩受到性骚扰，

78
00:04:15.403 --> 00:04:18.570
and they don't even tell their mothers.
而且她们甚至不会告诉她们的母亲。

79
00:04:19.445 --> 00:04:21.921
And it's the negative comments from others
同时也是来自其他人的负面评论

80
00:04:21.945 --> 00:04:26.653
that leads to 90 percent of women saying that they dislike their bodies.
让 90% 的女性说 她们嫌恶自己的身体。

81
00:04:27.278 --> 00:04:29.546
When a girl rejects her body,
当一个女孩排斥自己的身体时，

82
00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:31.629
she rejects her only house
她就是在排斥她唯一的“归宿”，

83
00:04:31.653 --> 00:04:34.546
and invisibility and insecurity
于是隐形和不自信

84
00:04:34.570 --> 00:04:37.213
become her very shaky foundation.
变成了她不稳定的基础。

85
00:04:37.237 --> 00:04:40.820
Habit two: Be quiet. Chup.
习惯二：安静。不要说话。

86
00:04:41.403 --> 00:04:43.379
If you're not supposed to exist
如果你不应该存在，

87
00:04:43.403 --> 00:04:45.004
and you don't have a body,
也不拥有一个身体，

88
00:04:45.028 --> 00:04:47.171
how can you have a voice?
那你怎会有声音呢？

89
00:04:47.195 --> 00:04:49.088
So just about every woman said,
几乎所有的女性都说，

90
00:04:48.956 --> 00:04:53.057
"When I was little, my mother used to scold me and say,
“我小时候，我妈妈经常责骂我：

91
00:04:53.278 --> 00:04:56.254
'Don't speak, be quiet, be chup,
’不要说话，保持安静，

92
00:04:55.676 --> 00:04:59.311
speak softly, don't argue and never answer back.
小声说话，不要争吵，不许顶嘴，

93
00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:01.129
Jawab nahi Dena.'"
不要说话。’ ”

94
00:05:01.153 --> 00:05:02.695
I'm sure you've all heard that.
你们肯定都听过。

95
00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:06.046
And so girls become afraid, and they withdraw.
所以很多女孩变得胆小畏缩。

96
00:05:06.070 --> 00:05:09.463
And they become quiet and they say,
她们变得低声细语，她们会说：

97
00:05:09.487 --> 00:05:11.296
"Let it go. Jaane do.
“别管了，别计较了。

98
00:05:11.320 --> 00:05:13.153
What's the point? Nobody listens."
争有什么用？没人会理我们。”

99
00:05:14.195 --> 00:05:16.004
Educated women said
受过教育的女性说

100
00:05:15.899 --> 00:05:18.721
that their number one problem
她们面临的最大问题

101
00:05:17.612 --> 00:05:20.879
was their inability to speak up,
就是不敢畅所欲言，

102
00:05:20.903 --> 00:05:23.796
as if there was a foot on their throat
如骨鲠在喉

103
00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:25.070
ready to choke them.
难以启齿。

104
00:05:26.070 --> 00:05:29.028
Silence slices off women.
沉默是女性的绊脚石。

105
00:05:31.195 --> 00:05:34.088
Habit three: Be a people pleaser.
习惯三：讨好别人。

106
00:05:33.945 --> 00:05:35.212
Please others.
讨好别人。

107
00:05:35.403 --> 00:05:38.546
Everyone likes a nice woman who always smiles,
所有人都喜欢面带微笑的温柔女子，

108
00:05:38.570 --> 00:05:41.004
who never says no, who is never angry,
从来不会说“不”，也从来不会生气，

109
00:05:40.950 --> 00:05:43.016
even when she's being exploited.
即使被别人欺负也不会生气的女子。

110
00:05:43.112 --> 00:05:45.838
Amisha, who is 18, said,
18 岁的 Amisha 说，

111
00:05:45.862 --> 00:05:48.129
"My father said,
“我的父亲常说，

112
00:05:48.153 --> 00:05:51.153
'If I don't see you smiling, I don't feel good.'"
‘如果我见你不笑，我就觉得别扭。’ ”

113
00:05:51.987 --> 00:05:53.296
So she smiles.
于是她就强颜欢笑。

114
00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:55.879
So her father is teaching her,
她的父亲正在教她——

115
00:05:55.903 --> 00:05:59.838
my happiness is more important than your happiness.
别人的快乐比自己的快乐更重要。

116
00:05:59.862 --> 00:06:04.088
And in this business of trying to make everyone happy all the time,
而在这种想方设法 让别人开心的环境中，

117
00:06:03.968 --> 00:06:06.923
girls become afraid to make decisions.
女孩变得害怕做决断。

118
00:06:07.862 --> 00:06:10.463
And when you ask them, they say,
当你问她们的时候，她们就说，

119
00:06:10.487 --> 00:06:12.862
"Anything, whatever! Kuch bhi!
“无所谓，随你。

120
00:06:13.737 --> 00:06:15.528
Everything goes. Chalta hai."
随便，我都行。”

121
00:06:16.903 --> 00:06:18.921
Darsha, who is 25,
25 岁的 Darsha 说，

122
00:06:18.945 --> 00:06:20.838
said with great pride,
非常自豪地说，

123
00:06:20.862 --> 00:06:23.338
"I'm highly elastic.
“我非常百变圆滑。

124
00:06:23.362 --> 00:06:26.612
I become whatever others want me to be."
我可以成为别人想让我成为的人。”

125
00:06:27.320 --> 00:06:30.046
Such girls give up their dreams,
这样的女孩放弃她们的梦想，

126
00:06:29.889 --> 00:06:31.256
their desires,
她们的追求，

127
00:06:31.403 --> 00:06:33.338
and nobody even notices,
也没有人会注意到，

128
00:06:33.362 --> 00:06:35.296
except for depression.
而这时，抑郁会降临。

129
00:06:35.320 --> 00:06:36.570
It moves in.
开始侵蚀女性。

130
00:06:37.403 --> 00:06:40.820
Another slice of a girl is taken off.
又一部分女孩被祸害了。

131
00:06:42.862 --> 00:06:45.570
Habit four: You have no sexuality.
习惯四：你没有性欲。

132
00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:50.921
I think you'd all agree that with a population of over 1.3 billion,
你们应该都知道 超过 13 亿人口的印度

133
00:06:50.945 --> 00:06:52.820
sex is not new to India.
对性都不陌生。

134
00:06:53.799 --> 00:06:58.618
What is new is that more people now acknowledge
现在越来越多的人开始认识到

135
00:06:58.778 --> 00:07:01.820
that women, too, have a right to sexual desire.
女性也有性欲权利。

136
00:07:02.862 --> 00:07:06.338
But how can a woman who has not been allowed to own her body,
但是如果一个女人 无法拥有自己的身体，

137
00:07:06.362 --> 00:07:08.796
who hasn't been educated about her body,
不了解自己的身体，

138
00:07:08.820 --> 00:07:11.296
who may have been sexually molested,
还有可能受过性侵，

139
00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:12.796
who cannot say no
她不会说“不”，

140
00:07:12.820 --> 00:07:15.004
and who has been filled with shame,
又带着羞耻感，

141
00:07:14.869 --> 00:07:17.358
how can she claim her sexual desire?
她如何表达自己的性欲？

142
00:07:18.237 --> 00:07:20.862
A woman's sexuality is suppressed.
女性的性欲受到压制。

143
00:07:22.445 --> 00:07:25.737
Habit five: Don't trust women.
习惯五：不要相信女性。

144
00:07:26.903 --> 00:07:29.254
Imagine how the world would change
想象一下这个世界 会发生多大的变化

145
00:07:29.278 --> 00:07:31.754
if women came together in solidarity,
一旦所有女性联手？

146
00:07:31.778 --> 00:07:34.588
but as to make sure that this doesn't happen,
但是为了确保这不会发生，

147
00:07:34.612 --> 00:07:38.088
our culture places high moral value
我们文化的价值观

148
00:07:37.943 --> 00:07:41.294
on loyalty to men and family secrecy.
极其强调对男人和家庭隐秘的忠诚。

149
00:07:41.945 --> 00:07:43.588
Woman after woman said,
许多女人说，

150
00:07:43.612 --> 00:07:46.213
"I know only one trustworthy woman,
“我只认识一个可靠的女人，

151
00:07:46.237 --> 00:07:47.838
and that's me."
那就是我自己。”

152
00:07:47.862 --> 00:07:49.379
Even Ruchi, who is 30
30 岁的 Ruchi ，

153
00:07:49.403 --> 00:07:53.296
and who works on women's empowerment at Delhi University, said,
她在德里大学研究赋权女性， 可连她都说，

154
00:07:53.320 --> 00:07:57.213
"I don't trust women. They're jealous and they backbite."
“我不相信其他女性， 她们都是嫉妒别人的两面派。”

155
00:07:57.237 --> 00:07:59.004
Obviously, then, in cities,
之后显然，在城市中，

156
00:07:58.869 --> 00:08:00.855
women don't join women's groups,
女性不会加入女性群体，

157
00:08:00.903 --> 00:08:04.153
and when you ask them why, they say, "We don't have time for gossip."
当你问她们为什么的时候， 她们就说：“我们没时间去八卦。”

158
00:08:04.956 --> 00:08:09.057
It's much easier  to demolish a woman who is alone.
打败一个孤身的女子 可就容易多了。

159
00:08:10.195 --> 00:08:13.737
Habit six: Duty over desire.
习惯六：职责大于欲望。

160
00:08:14.653 --> 00:08:18.963
Muskan gave a very long definition of a good girl, and she's only 15.
年仅 15 岁的 Muskan 给出了 一个很长的”好姑娘“的诠释。

161
00:08:18.987 --> 00:08:21.588
"She is kind, gentle, polite, loving,
”她必须善良、温柔、有礼、贤淑、

162
00:08:21.612 --> 00:08:24.046
caring, truthful, obedient, respects elders,
关怀、诚实、温顺、敬重老人、

163
00:08:24.070 --> 00:08:27.737
helps everyone unconditionally, and is good to others and fulfills duty."
无条件地帮助他人， 慈悲心肠，履行义务。”

164
00:08:29.487 --> 00:08:31.379
Tiring, isn't it.
听上去很累，不是吗？

165
00:08:31.403 --> 00:08:34.338
By the time you fulfill duty,
等你履行完职责后，

166
00:08:34.362 --> 00:08:37.796
whatever little desire is left is also lost.
不论你还有多小的欲望留存， 也已因此消失殆尽了。

167
00:08:37.820 --> 00:08:41.338
And when sacrificing mothers have nothing left to say
牺牲其一生的母亲们 也没有其他的话可说了，

168
00:08:41.362 --> 00:08:43.046
except talk about food --
除了谈到饭食——

169
00:08:43.070 --> 00:08:47.004
"Have you eaten? Khana kha liya? What will you eat?" --
“你吃过了吗？你想吃什么？”

170
00:08:46.911 --> 00:08:51.148
men like Saurabh, who is 24, call them "boring."
24 岁的小伙子 Saurabh  说她们很“无趣”。

171
00:08:52.237 --> 00:08:54.796
A woman becomes a residue.
女性变成了残渣。

172
00:08:54.820 --> 00:08:59.004
Habit seven: Be totally dependent.
习惯七：完全依赖他人。

173
00:08:58.953 --> 00:09:02.037
So all these habits collectively crush women,
所有这些习惯都压制着女性，

174
00:09:02.153 --> 00:09:03.671
fill her with fear
让她充满恐惧，

175
00:09:03.695 --> 00:09:07.296
and make her totally dependent on men for her survival,
让她为了生存而完全依靠男人，

176
00:09:07.320 --> 00:09:10.987
and this allows the system of male power to continue.
这便允许了男权制度的延续。

177
00:09:11.903 --> 00:09:16.421
So all these seven habits that we thought were good and moral
这些我们起初认为是 合乎正道的七个好习惯

178
00:09:16.445 --> 00:09:19.338
snatch life away from girls
剥夺了女性的生命

179
00:09:19.362 --> 00:09:21.778
and position men to abuse.
让男性肆意践踏。

180
00:09:22.945 --> 00:09:24.796
We must change.
我们必须做出改变。

181
00:09:24.820 --> 00:09:26.070
How do we change?
我们如何改变呢？

182
00:09:26.903 --> 00:09:28.737
A habit is just a habit.
习惯只是一个习惯而已。

183
00:09:29.528 --> 00:09:31.921
Every habit is a learned habit,
所有习惯都是学来的，

184
00:09:31.945 --> 00:09:33.504
so we can unlearn them
所以我们也可以忘记它们，

185
00:09:33.528 --> 00:09:36.213
and this personal change is extremely important.
这样的自我改变是十分重要的。

186
00:09:36.237 --> 00:09:38.338
I had to change too.
我也必须改变。

187
00:09:38.362 --> 00:09:40.921
But this doesn't change the system
但是这都无法改变这个

188
00:09:40.945 --> 00:09:43.237
that crushes millions of other women.
压制无数女性的系统。

189
00:09:44.112 --> 00:09:46.213
So we have to go to the roots.
所以我们要找到根源。

190
00:09:46.237 --> 00:09:50.629
We must change what it means to be a good woman and a good man,
我们必须改变 “好女人和好男人”的定义，

191
00:09:50.653 --> 00:09:53.403
because this a foundation of every society.
因为这是每一个社会的基础。

192
00:09:54.112 --> 00:09:58.504
We don't need elastic women, we need elastic definitions,
我们不需要百变的女性， 我们需要百变的定义，

193
00:09:58.528 --> 00:10:00.088
for men too,
对男人也是，

194
00:10:00.112 --> 00:10:05.338
and this big societal change cannot happen without men's involvement.
这样巨大的社会观变化 离不开男人的参与。

195
00:10:05.362 --> 00:10:06.629
We need you.
我们需要你们。

196
00:10:06.653 --> 00:10:09.671
We need men to become champions of change,
我们需要男人加入我们的运动，

197
00:10:09.695 --> 00:10:12.879
to develop strong change muscles.
来发扬壮大我们的运动。

198
00:10:12.903 --> 00:10:15.421
Otherwise, it will be two more centuries
要不然，我们要再等两个世纪

199
00:10:15.445 --> 00:10:17.796
before our girls, and our boys,
才能看到我们的儿女

200
00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:19.070
are safe and free.
获得安全和自由。

201
00:10:20.112 --> 00:10:26.379
Imagine half a billion women coming together, with the support of men,
试想一下，五亿女性团结在一起， 有着男性的支持，

202
00:10:26.403 --> 00:10:29.504
to talk to one another for conversation, for change,
共同探讨，一起变化，

203
00:10:29.528 --> 00:10:31.421
both personal and political,
改变自己，改变政见，

204
00:10:31.445 --> 00:10:33.796
and imagine men in their own circles,
男人们也加入这个圈子，

205
00:10:33.820 --> 00:10:38.088
and imagine women and men coming together to just listen to each other
女性和男性一起倾听对方，

206
00:10:38.112 --> 00:10:40.504
without judgment, without blame,
没有偏见，没有责备，

207
00:10:40.528 --> 00:10:43.338
without accusations and without shame.
没有怪罪，没有羞耻。

208
00:10:43.362 --> 00:10:45.421
Imagine how much we would change.
想象一下我们能做出多少变化。

209
00:10:45.445 --> 00:10:47.338
We can do this together.
我们可以一起实现这一切。

210
00:10:47.362 --> 00:10:49.778
Women, don't adjust.
女性们，别再适应。

211
00:10:50.987 --> 00:10:52.903
Men, adjust.
男性们，去适应。

212
00:10:53.778 --> 00:10:55.546
It's time.
我们的时间到了。

213
00:10:55.570 --> 00:10:56.921
Thank you.
谢谢。

214
00:10:56.945 --> 00:11:00.778
(Applause)
（掌声）

215
00:11:01.362 --> 00:11:02.995
SRK: How well said, how wonderful.
汗：说得好！

216
00:11:02.995 --> 00:11:04.757
Everyone, Deepa, please.
再次把掌声给迪帕！

217
00:11:04.820 --> 00:11:06.629
Listening to her, I realized
听完你的演讲，我发现

218
00:11:06.653 --> 00:11:10.213
that even in the simplest conversations that we have with women,
即使和女性最普通的对话中，

219
00:11:10.237 --> 00:11:11.796
we're actually being aggressive.
我们也经常气势汹汹。

220
00:11:11.820 --> 00:11:14.713
For example, I do tell my daughter sometimes,
比方说，我有时确实会对我女儿说，

221
00:11:14.737 --> 00:11:17.879
"Yaar Tu hasti hai to mujhe accha lagta hai varna bura lagta hai".
“如果你是我， 你会觉得开心还是不开心？”

222
00:11:17.903 --> 00:11:19.504
So sorry, I would never do that.
抱歉，我以后再也不会了。

223
00:11:19.528 --> 00:11:21.588
Aaj Se main meri beti ko yahi bolunga.
从今天起，我要对我的女儿说，

224
00:11:21.612 --> 00:11:22.921
Whatever you're doing,
”无论你做什么，

225
00:11:22.945 --> 00:11:25.546
mujhe accha hi lagta hai, aur accha nahi bhi lagta hai
都不是为了让我开心，

226
00:11:25.570 --> 00:11:28.421
Toh mera kya, tum wohi karo jo tumhare ko lagta hai, right?
只要你觉得自己开心就好，对吗？”

227
00:11:28.445 --> 00:11:31.338
(Applause)
（掌声）

228
00:11:31.362 --> 00:11:32.838
How did you feel,
汗：您自己有何感想，

229
00:11:32.862 --> 00:11:38.796
first listening to so many unfulfilled stories, desires,
听到那么多未实现的故事、理想，

230
00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:40.129
lack of independence,
还有独立性缺失，

231
00:11:40.153 --> 00:11:44.671
of girls that you normally would assume we think these girls are better off?
这些我们本以为是好姑娘的典范？

232
00:11:44.695 --> 00:11:46.201
DN: Very depressed.
迪：感到非常抑郁。

233
00:11:46.201 --> 00:11:49.088
It was shocking for me, and that's why I couldn't stop,
我觉得非常震惊， 所以我不能停下来，

234
00:11:49.112 --> 00:11:53.088
because I had no plans to do a study and no plans to write a book.
因为我没有计划做一个调研， 也没有计划写书。

235
00:11:53.112 --> 00:11:56.921
I'd written 17 books before, and I thought, "I'm done,"
我之前出版了17本书， 我对自己说：“我做完了。”

236
00:11:56.945 --> 00:11:59.088
but when I went to St. Stephen's College
但是当我去圣斯蒂芬学院的时候，

237
00:11:59.112 --> 00:12:04.213
and I heard, at most elite colleges you well know from Delhi,
我在德里的大多数高级学府中，

238
00:12:04.237 --> 00:12:06.296
and the young women and the men,
这些年轻人

239
00:12:06.320 --> 00:12:10.171
what they said about what it meant to them to be a woman and man
所说的什么是好女人，好男人

240
00:12:10.195 --> 00:12:13.463
sounded not like me but like my mother's generation.
听上去不像是我， 而是像我的母亲那代人的看法。

241
00:12:13.487 --> 00:12:16.588
So then I went to another college and another college.
所以我去了一个又一个学院。

242
00:12:16.612 --> 00:12:18.296
The thing that was striking to me
让我最震惊的是

243
00:12:18.320 --> 00:12:21.754
is that each woman felt she was alone,
每个女性都觉得她是孤独的，

244
00:12:21.778 --> 00:12:25.171
that she hides her fear and hides her behavior,
她隐藏着自己的恐惧， 隐藏自己的行为，

245
00:12:25.195 --> 00:12:27.195
because she thinks it's a personal fault.
因为她觉得自己是一个缺憾。

246
00:12:27.945 --> 00:12:30.879
It's not a personal fault, it's training,
这不是一个缺憾，是后天导致的，

247
00:12:30.903 --> 00:12:33.213
and I think that's the biggest revelation
而且我最大的发现是

248
00:12:33.237 --> 00:12:36.671
is that, if we stop pretending,
如果我们不再伪装，

249
00:12:36.695 --> 00:12:38.421
then the world changes.
那这个世界就会改变。

250
00:12:38.445 --> 00:12:41.129
SRK: Do you girls all agree with what Deepa is saying?
汗：你们都同意迪帕的说法吗？

251
00:12:41.153 --> 00:12:44.004
(Applause)
（掌声）

252
00:12:43.953 --> 00:12:45.678
Already see that young girl saying,
已经看到有姑娘说，

253
00:12:45.778 --> 00:12:48.379
"Heard, heard what she said? You say this to me."
“听到没，听到没？ 你要这样和我说话。”

254
00:12:48.403 --> 00:12:50.088
Yeah, that's the way it should be.
对，就应该是这样。

255
00:12:49.930 --> 00:12:52.680
You, boy, you adjust. We are not adjusting anymore, OK?
你们男性应该去适应， 我们不该再继续适应下去了。

256
00:12:52.862 --> 00:12:54.421
(Applause)
（掌声）

257
00:12:54.445 --> 00:12:56.796
Thank you so much. Have a good evening. Thank you.
非常感谢您！谢谢！

258
00:12:56.820 --> 00:12:57.970
(Applause)
（掌声）